claims:
Claims Claims 1. A computer-implemented method comprising: receiving a request from a user to present at least one profile similar to the user's profile, wherein each profile represents a member of a social networking service; determining a relevance score for each of a plurality of profiles, wherein the relevance score for a profile indicates a degree of similarity between that profile and the user's profile, wherein determining the relevance score for a profile comprises: extracting a value for one or more features from the profile; normalising each feature value to generate a normalized feature value; comparing one or more normalized feature values of the profile with values of equivalent features of the user's profile based on user-defmeable settings to obtain a similarity value for each feature; and aggregating the similarity values based on the user-defmeable settings to determine a relevance score for the profile; selectively presenting one or more profiles to the user based on the determined relevance scores of the profiles and the user-defmeable settings; allowing the user to request a connection with a member represented by each presented profile. 2. The method of claim 1, wherein the user-defmeable settings comprise a location radius setting which indicates a location radius of interest to the user, and wherein selectively presenting one or more profiles to the user comprises determining the location of a member represented by each profile and excluding profiles of members whose location is outside the location radius. 3. The method of claim 1, wherein the user-defmeable settings may comprise a threshold relevance setting, which indicates a threshold relevance score of interest to the user, and wherein selectively presenting one or more profiles to the user comprises excluding profiles having a relevance score below the threshold relevance score. 4. The method of claim 1, wherein the user-defmeable settings may comprise one or more keywords, indicating features of interest to the user, and wherein determining the relevance score for each of a plurality of profiles comprises increasing the relevance score of profiles that include the one or more keywords. 5. The method of claim 1, wherein determining a relevance score for a profile comprises computing one or more additional feature values from the profile based on information in the profile. 6. The method of claim 5, wherein the additional feature value is an estimate of overall profile relevance calculated based on a term frequency algorithm. 7. The method of claim 5, wherein the additional feature value is a skill class determined based on one or more skills contained in the profile, wherein the skill class is a machine learning based classifier. 8. The method of claim 1, wherein the user-defmeable settings comprise an indication of one or more features for comparison, and comparing one or more normalized feature values of a profile with values of equivalent features of the user's profile comprises comparing the values of the features indicated by the user-defmeable settings. 9. The method of claim 1, wherein one or more algorithms is applied in determining a similarity value for a feature, and comparing one or more normalized feature values of a profile with values of equivalent features of the user's profile comprises applying the one or more algorithms to obtain one or more similarity values for the feature. 10. The method of claim 9, wherein an algorithm weighting is applied to each algorithm and the method may further comprise applying the algorithm weighting to the similarity value obtained using the respective algorithm, and aggregating the weighted similarity values to obtain an aggregated similarity value for that feature. 11. The method of claim 1 , wherein the user-defmeable settings comprise an indication of a feature weighting to be applied to the similarity value for each feature, and aggregating the similarity values comprises applying the indicated feature weighting to each similarity value to obtain a weighted similarity value and combining the weighted similarity values to determine a relevance score for the profile. 12. The method of claim 11, wherein combining the weighted similarity values comprises computing a weighted average of the similarity values. 13. A computer-implemented method comprising: receiving a request from a user to present at least one community profile similar to the user's profile, wherein each community profile represents a virtual community within a social networking service; determining a relevance score for each of a plurality of community profiles, wherein the relevance score for a community profile indicates a degree of similarity between that community profile and the user's profile, wherein determining the relevance score for a community profile comprises: extracting a value for one or more features from the community profile; normalising each feature value to generate a normalized feature value; comparing one or more normalized feature values of the community profile with values of equivalent features of the user's profile based on user- defmeable settings to obtain a similarity value for each feature; and aggregating the similarity values based on the user-defmeable settings to determine a relevance score for the community profile; selectively presenting one or more community profiles to the user based on the determined relevance scores of the community profiles and the user-defmeable settings; allowing the user to request to join the community represented by each presented community profile. 14. A computer-implemented method comprising: determining a relevance score for each of a plurality of profiles, wherein the relevance score for a profile indicates a degree of similarity between that profile and a 

 community profile and wherein each profile represents a member of a social networking service and wherein the community profile represents a virtual community within the social networking service and wherein at least one of the member profiles represents a member of the social networking service who is a member of the community and at least one of the member profiles represents a member of the social networking service who is not a member of the community, wherein determining the relevance score for a profile comprises: extracting a value for one or more features from the profile; normalising each feature value to generate a normalized feature value; comparing one or more normalized feature values of the profile with values of equivalent features of the community profile based on user-defmeable settings to obtain a similarity value for each feature; and aggregating the similarity values based on the user-defmeable settings to determine a relevance score for the profile; comparing the relevance scores for members of the social networking service who are not members of the community with relevance scores for members of the social networking service who are members of the community; selectively inviting members of the social networking service who are not members of the community to join the community based on the comparison. 15. A non-transitory computer-readable medium storing executable instructions thereon, which, when executed by a processor, cause the processor to perform operations including: receiving a request from a user to present at least one profile similar to the user's profile, wherein each profile represents a member of a social networking service; determining a relevance score for each of a plurality of profiles, wherein the relevance score for a profile indicates a degree of similarity between that profile and the user's profile, wherein determining the relevance score for a profile comprises: extracting a value for one or more features from the profile; normalising each feature value to generate a normalized feature value; 

 comparing one or more normalized feature values of the profile with values of equivalent features of the user's profile based on user-defineable settings to obtain a similarity value for each feature; and aggregating the similarity values based on the user-defineable settings to determine a relevance score for the profile; selectively presenting one or more profiles to the user based on the determined relevance scores of the profiles and the user-defineable settings; allowing the user to request a connection with each presented profile. 16. A non-transitory computer-readable medium storing executable instructions thereon, which, when executed by a processor, cause the processor to perform operations including: receiving a request from a user to present at least one community profile similar to the user's profile, wherein each community profile represents a virtual community within a social networking service; determining a relevance score for each of a plurality of community profiles, wherein the relevance score for a community profile indicates a degree of similarity between that community profile and the user's profile, wherein determining the relevance score for a community profile comprises: extracting a value for one or more features from the community profile; normalising each feature value to generate a normalized feature value; comparing one or more normalized feature values of the community profile with values of equivalent features of the user's profile based on user- defineable settings to obtain a similarity value for each feature; and aggregating the similarity values based on the user-defineable settings to determine a relevance score for the community profile; selectively presenting one or more community profiles to the user based on the determined relevance scores of the community profiles and the user-defineable settings; allowing the user to request to join the community represented by each presented community profile. 17. A non-transitory computer-readable medium storing executable instructions thereon, which, when executed by a processor, cause the processor to perform operations including: determining a relevance score for each of a plurality of profiles, wherein the relevance score for a profile indicates a degree of similarity between that profile and a community profile and wherein each profile represents a member of a social networking service and wherein the community profile represents a virtual community within the social networking service and wherein at least one of the member profiles represents a member of the social networking service who is a member of the community and at least one of the member profiles represents a member of the social networking service who is not a member of the community, wherein determining the relevance score for a profile comprises: extracting a value for one or more features from the profile; normalising each feature value to generate a normalized feature value; comparing one or more normalized feature values of the profile with values of equivalent features of the community profile based on user-defmeable settings to obtain a similarity value for each feature; and aggregating the similarity values based on the user-defmeable settings to determine a relevance score for the profile; comparing the relevance scores for members of the social networking service who are not members of the community with relevance scores for members of the social networking service who are members of the community; selectively inviting members of the social networking service who are not members of the community to join the community based on the comparison.
